[BoardVersionToken "edf1f3dd9ee15c7d82e9fabfa45f24585b52ccc573498a205cea005ca517f220"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/preemptive_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

You open 3\D. North doubles, partner raises to 4\D, and South bids 4\H.  

You just pass. Partner's raise was probably just advancing your preempt and they got to 4\H anyway. Sometimes preempts don't do the full job.

It is partner's decision, not yours, whether to continue to 5\D as a sacrifice.}

